<p class=3D"rubric">References</p>
<p>For n_components =3D=3D =E2=80=98mle=E2=80=99, this class uses the metho=
d from:
<a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://tminka.github.io/papers/pca=
/minka-pca.pdf">Minka, T. P.. =E2=80=9CAutomatic choice of dimensionality f=
or PCA=E2=80=9D.
In NIPS, pp. 598-604</a></p>
<p>Implements the probabilistic PCA model from:
<a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"http://www.miketipping.com/papers/m=
et-mppca.pdf">Tipping, M. E., and Bishop, C. M. (1999). =E2=80=9CProbabilis=
tic principal
component analysis=E2=80=9D. Journal of the Royal Statistical Society:
Series B (Statistical Methodology), 61(3), 611-622.</a>
via the score and score_samples methods.</p>
<p>For svd_solver =3D=3D =E2=80=98arpack=E2=80=99, refer to <code class=3D"=
docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">scipy.sparse.linalg.svds<=
/span></code>.</p>
<p>For svd_solver =3D=3D =E2=80=98randomized=E2=80=99, see:
<a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://doi.org/10.1137/090771806">=
Halko, N., Martinsson, P. G., and Tropp, J. A. (2011).
=E2=80=9CFinding structure with randomness: Probabilistic algorithms for
constructing approximate matrix decompositions=E2=80=9D.
SIAM review, 53(2), 217-288.</a>
and also
<a class=3D"reference external" href=3D"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.acha.2010=
.02.003">Martinsson, P. G., Rokhlin, V., and Tygert, M. (2011).
=E2=80=9CA randomized algorithm for the decomposition of matrices=E2=80=9D.
Applied and Computational Harmonic Analysis, 30(1), 47-68.</a></p>
